<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; 'CAGNEY & LACEY' REUNITE FOR TWO HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fans of "Cagney & Lacey," the police drama that ran from 1982 through 1988 on 
CBS, are in for a treat Sunday at 9 p.m. when the network offers "Cagney & 
Lacey: The Return."The two-hour movie reunites Chris (Sharon Gless), now an 
investigator for the district attorney's office, and retired Mary Beth (Tyne 
Daly). Channels 2 and 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Vice President Al Gore analyzes the Democrats' chances Tuesday on "Both Sides 
With Jesse Jackson," today at 2:30 p.m. on CNN. 
</P>
<P>
 President Clinton appears on a special edition of "Larry King Live," Sunday 
from Seattle, to give his election expectations, at 6 p.m. on CNN. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
