</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; WASHINGTON, D.C.; CRACKS INSPECTED IN VIETNAM MEMORIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A survey team started checking crack damage in the Vietnam Veterans Memorial 
to determine if panels should be repaired or replaced.Architects and engineers 
from the National Park Service began the task with special cameras and 
equipment. They are inspecting hairline cracks in some of the black reflective 
panels that make up the 500-foot-long wall inscribed with the names of over 
58,200 American soldiers who died or are missing in Southeast Asia. The cause 
of the splits is not known. 
</P>
