<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; CITY COUNCIL OPPOSES SMOKING 
INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joining forces with other cities in the county, the Port Hueneme City Council 
unanimously agreed to oppose Proposition 188, which would permit smoking in 
some public places where it is now prohibited. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Ken Hess said he opposed the proposition because it robs local 
governments of the ability to pass their own laws. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposition "is trying to usurp the authority of local governments," Hess 
said. "They are telling us how to make rules in our own cities, and that is not 
right." 
</P>
<P>
 Although smoking is not allowed in city-owned buildings in Port Hueneme, 
restaurants are allowed to have smoking areas. 
</P>
<P>
 If Proposition 188 is passed on the November ballot, it would nullify local 
laws on smoking and tobacco, and, among other things, allow smoking in office 
lounges. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
