<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; ELEMENTARY SCHOOL PUTS OUT NEWSPAPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sixth-graders at Las Palmas Elementary School have put out their first edition 
of the Las Palmas Times, written exclusively by and for students. 
</P>
<P>
 The volunteer staff includes 53 of the school's 60 sixth-grade students, 
Principal Doug Kramer said. 
</P>
<P>
 The newspaper is a cooperative project involving the school, a community 
newspaper, a printing company and Saddleback College's journalism department. 
</P>
<P>
 For a free copy of the paper, call Las Palmas Elementary at (714) 492-3456. 
JEFF BEAN 
