<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viacom Selling TV Network Affiliates: The company said it is negotiating the 
sale of its five affiliates but would not say to whom or at what price.The 
entertainment newspaper Daily Variety put the asking price at nearly $400 
million. The stations are in Shreveport, La.; Hartford, Conn.; Rochester and 
Albany, N.Y., and St. Louis. Since it won control of Paramount Communications 
Inc. earlier this year, Viacom Inc. has sold New York's Madison Square Garden, 
the MSG sports network and the New York Knicks basketball and Rangers hockey 
teams to Cablevision Systems and ITT Corp. for $1.1 billion. Viacom is seeking 
to sell its cable systems to a Tele-Communications Inc.-backed joint venture 
for at least $1 billion. 
</P>
