<TEXT>
<P>
 Carolco to Make Interest Payments: The movie producer, which has been 
struggling to raise cash, said it will pay interest on some of its subordinated 
notes and senior notes.The payments were due Oct. 15, though Carolco was 
allowed a 30-day grace period. Japan's Pioneer, Carolco's largest shareholder, 
agreed to advance the company as much as $8 million in license fees. Carolco 
also sold its film "Showgirls" to France's Chargeurs in exchange for production 
costs spent to date. North American distribution rights have just been acquired 
by MGM/UA. 
</P>
