<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOT IN CARJACKING ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man opened fire on a motorist, seriously wounding him, after the driver 
refused to surrender his car, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorist, Mario Ayala, believed to be in his 20s, remained in serious 
condition at Northridge Hospital Medical Center on Friday with a bullet wound 
to his chest, police said.He is expected to recover, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman fled after the attack, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred about 8:45 p.m. Thursday as Ayala and a friend were 
driving his newly purchased car -- a purple 1988 Nissan Sentra with custom 
rims, said LAPD Detective Mel Arnold. As they drove down the 7800 block of 
Peachtree Avenue, a man walked into the middle of the street, and Ayala, 
thinking it was a friend, stopped the car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, however, drew a pistol and demanded that Ayala give him the car, 
Arnold said. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead, police said Ayala stepped on the accelerator and the gunman fired 
several shots through the windshield.  
</P>
<P>
 Ayala, who was wounded, continued driving for about a block until the car 
slammed into a fire hydrant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 His friend was not hurt, Arnold said. Police have no suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
