<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; AH SIGH WINS ED BURKE FUTURITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Favored Ah Sigh won her seventh race in eight career starts in the $185,000 Ed 
Burke Memorial Futurity on Friday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by John Creager, Ah Sigh broke perfectly from the inside post position, 
immediately taking charge of the 350-yard race.The First Down Dash filly was 
never challenged, finishing nearly a length in front of runner-up The Fling 
King. Fruitstand Johnny, who was claimed for $6,250 in August, finished third.  
</P>
<P>
 Trained by Charlie Bloomquist for owner Frank Nakamura, Ah Sigh posted a 
winning time of 17.63 seconds, and paid $3.40, $2.80, and $2.20. Ah Sigh 
previously won the Miss Kindergarten Futurity and finished third in the 
Governor's Cup Futurity, making her one of the top 2-year-old fillies in the 
nation. 
</P>
<P>
 Creager, who is serving a suspension for an incident last weekend on Griswold, 
was given clearance to ride in the Ed Burke. Several fans were obviously still 
upset with Creager, jeering at the jockey as he returned to the winner's circle 
on Ah Sigh. STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
