<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; MUSICAL QUARTERBACKS KEY TRABUCO HILLS, 
34-10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 J.C. Pintsak threw for three touchdowns and 145 yards to lead visiting Trabuco 
Hills to a 34-10 victory over host San Clemente Friday night in a South Coast 
League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills shuffled its quarterbacks, Pintsak and Chad Collins, on every 
play, keeping the Tritons off balance all night.Collins connected on four of 
six passes for 80 yards and one touchdown. The Mustangs had 225 yards passing 
in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Pintsak came out throwing on his first possession, connecting with Laquent 
Fobbs on a 65-yard pass for a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Pintsak went to the air again on the Mustangs' third series, connecting on key 
passes to Jake Anderson. A 15-yard slant pass across the middle to Anderson set 
up Trabuco Hills' next score. DeSha Runnels' one-yard plunge put Trabuco Hills 
ahead, 14-0, with 3 minutes 45 seconds remaining in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente made the score 14-7 seconds before the end of the quarter on a 
four-yard run by Trevor Insley. The Tritons' 13-play, 84-yard scoring drive was 
led by Keith Gros' 45 yards rushing. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills' Pintsak found Fobbs for his second touchdown of the night, a 
19-yard pass play for a 20-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Fobbs caught a game-high 101 yards, averaging nearly 34 yards for his three 
receptions. 
</P>
<P>
 Pintsak and Collins each threw for touchdowns in the third quarter to put 
Trabuco Hills ahead, 34-10. Pintsak connected with Brian Flourney from 24 
yards, while Anderson and Collins teamed up on a 21-yard play. RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Prep Sports 
</P>
