<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANYON SECURES PLAYOFF BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With third place in the Foothill League and a playoff berth on the line, 
visiting Canyon High rose to the occasion Friday and played an almost-flawless 
second half in a 27-12 victory over Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior quarterback Ahjeron Palmer completed seven of 14 passes for 118 yards 
and three touchdowns and rushed eight times for 76 yards to lead the Cowboys 
(3-5-1, 2-2 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
 Senior tight end Tim Fitzgerald also played a key role, with four receptions 
for 89 yards, including touchdown catches of seven and 16 yards, and a 35-yard 
reception that set up the second Canyon score. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank (3-6, 0-3) struck first on Jason Jonas' one-yard run six minutes into 
the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cowboys took the lead 8 minutes 26 seconds into the second quarter on a 
seven-yard pass from Palmer to Fitzgerald. 
</P>
</TEXT>
