<HEADLINE>
<P>
HART'S 42-7 ROUT SETS UP A SHOWDOWN FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Steve McKeon completed 14 of 17 passes for 223 yards and two touchdowns and 
fullback Ted Iacenda scored four touchdowns to lead Hart High to a 42-7 victory 
over Burroughs in a Foothill League game Friday night at College of the 
Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first football game played at Canyons this season because the 
school's stadium was damaged in the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory sets up a showdown between Hart and Saugus next week. Hart is 9-0 
and 3-0 in league play. Saugus, also 3-0 in league play, had a bye Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Iacenda, who finished with 58 yards in 12 carries, had a two-yard scoring run 
and two one-yard scoring runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Iacenda also caught a three-yard touchdown pass from McKeon, which gave Hart a 
28-0 lead with 1 minute 27 seconds left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart increased its lead to 35-0 when J.B. Nelson returned the second half 
kickoff 93 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs (2-7, 0-3) scored on a 16-yard pass play from quarterback Mike 
Barrett to wide receiver Scott Boldvich with 2:47 left in the third quarter. 
Boldvich finished with six catches for 111 yards. Barrett completed 12 of 30 
passes for 220 yards, 171 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart scored on five of its first six possessions. 
</P>
<P>
 The Indians took a 14-0 lead when McKeon connected with wide receiver Tim 
Waddell on a 19-yard pass play with 4:19 left in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart's Domenic Delillio led all receivers with six receptions for 143 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs running back Carlos Moreno had 63 yards in 19 carries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
