<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Royal 14, Thousand Oaks 12 -- Royal scored on a 65-yard pass play from Wes 
Lagatta to Brendan Gibson on the game's first play and held off a rally by host 
Thousand Oaks. Thousand Oaks (3-5, 2-4) drove deep into Royal territory on 
seven of its 10 possessions, but could not score until midway through the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Rob Read recovered Highlander running back Jerome Lee's third fumble and Bill 
Sperry scored on a 10-yard sweep one play later to cut Royal's lead to 14-6. 
The point-after attempt sailed wide left. 
</P>
<P>
 Read sacked Lagatta on the next series, forcing a Highlander punt. Sophomore 
quarterback Scott McEwan marched Thousand Oaks 74 yards in five plays, capped 
by a 45-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver Eric Allen with 3:35 to play. The 
conversion pass failed, and Royal ran out the clock. 
</P>
<P>
 Lagatta connected on six of nine passes for 180 yards. Gibson had four catches 
for 107 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Ange caught three passes for 100 yards for Thousand Oaks. Sperry 
intercepted two passes and linebacker Greg Gallup recovered two fumbles. GREG 
MEADE 
</P>
</TEXT>
