<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FREEWAY LEAGUE; BUENA PARK SHAKES OFF 
MONTGOMERY AND UPSETS TROY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buena Park survived a 213-yard rushing performance by Troy's Larry Montgomery 
and upset the Warriors, 17-14, Friday at Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The Coyotes (3-6, 2-2) moved into a tie for second place with Troy (6-3, 2-2), 
Sunny Hills and Fullerton in the Freeway League. 
</P>
<P>
 Corey Lyday opened the game with a 91-yard kickoff return to the Buena Park 
four and a penalty moved the ball to the two, but it took seven minutes and 
another possession before Buena Park scored. The Troy defense stopped four 
rushing attempts by quarterback David Barrios and took over on the one. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors eventually punted to the 37 and Buena Park scored with five 
minutes left in the first quarter on a three-yard run by Tim Jones. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy countered with a 30-yard touchdown run by Montgomery with 3:03 left in 
the quarter. Darrell Cahoon blocked the conversion attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park increased its lead to 14-6 when Barrios hit a wide-open Michael 
Cade, who outraced the Troy defense for a 67-yard scoring pass. 
</P>
<P>
 Jude Reyes made a 36-yard field goal with three minutes left in the half for 
Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Reyes made a 23-yard field goal early in the third quarter, but the Coyotes 
accepted a roughing-the-kicker penalty and then fumbled the ball away on the 
next play. 
</P>
<P>
 Troy put together a 91-yard drive with Montgomery scoring from the two and 
adding a two-point conversion with 3:33 left in the third quarter, reducing the 
lead to 17-14. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
