<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SUNNY HILLS SCORES ON SIX CONSECUTIVE 
POSSESSIONS, ROUTS LA HABRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunny Hills kept its playoff hopes alive with a 40-10 victory over La Habra in 
a Freeway League game Friday night at La Habra High. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra took a 10-0 lead into the second quarter.But then Sunny Hills scored 
touchdowns on six consecutive possessions, led by three rushing touchdowns from 
junior Chris Velotta. 
</P>
<P>
 "This year we've had a lot of games decided by seven or less points," Sunny 
Hills Coach Tim Devaney said. "It was nice to see our offense open up and score 
the way we did." 
</P>
<P>
 Down, 10-0, Sunny Hills scored when Velotta scored on a seven-yard run. Sunny 
Hills would take the lead for good three minutes later when quarterback Greg 
Garand completed a 56-yard scoring pass to Jeff Renaud. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive lineman Brian Miklos returned a fumble 48 yards to increase the 
Lancer lead to 20-10. Velotta scored his second touchdown run, again from seven 
yards, with 1:07 remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills (3-6, 2-2) completed its scoring in the third quarter on a 
one-yard quarterback sneak by Garand and a 57-yard run by Velotta. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra (3-6, 1-3) scored all its points in the first quarter. Chris Diaz 
kicked a 44-yard field goal and quarterback Nick Armstrong scored on a one-yard 
run. DALE RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
