<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; GOLDEN WEST LEAGUE; HERNANDEZ'S THREE 
SCORES LEAD SADDLEBACK VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hector Hernandez scored three touchdowns as Saddleback beat Santa Ana, 35-7, 
Friday night at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory moved the Roadrunners (3-6, 2-2) into third place in the Golden 
West League and they play Tustin next week for a playoff berth. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saints (2-7, 1-3) scored first when Byron Cabrera rushed 10 yards for a 
7-0 lead. Saddleback tied the score with 23 seconds left in the first quarter 
when Hernandez caught a 12-yard touchdown pass from Danny Rodriguez. 
</P>
<P>
 The Roadrunners took a 14-7 halftime lead when Omar Palacios scored on a 
23-yard touchdown run with 2:36 left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback dominated the second half, scoring three third-quarter touchdowns 
and allowing the Saints only 57 total yards in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The first touchdown was an 11-yard run by Palacios with 7:41 left in the 
quarter that gave the Roadrunners a 21-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Then Hernandez scored twice in 14 seconds. The first came when Rodriguez found 
him in the end zone with a 23-yard pass. Two plays later, Hernandez intercepted 
a Brian Schwalm pass and returned the ball 35 yards for a touchdown with 5:11 
left in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Palacios finished with 113 yards rushing. Teammate Danny Verino rushed for 106 
yards. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
