<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; ARMENDARIZ'S TOUCHDOWN, INTERCEPTION 
SPARK CENTURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sometimes you can't tell a player with a program. 
</P>
<P>
 Take Zeke Armendariz, for instance. 
</P>
<P>
 There was No. 53 for Century scoring a touchdown on a fumble recovery and 
intercepting a pass to pace the Centurions (5-4, 3-1) to a 17-7 victory over 
Katella (0-9, 0-4) Friday night in Empire League play at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 This sets up an Empire League title showdown next week, when Century plays 
Kennedy and El Dorado plays Loara. All four teams are 3-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 The program had No. 53 as Carlos Martinez. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Brown, Century's coach, said, "That roster was from an old program." 
</P>
<P>
 But there was no mistaking Armendariz's contributions. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-2, 203-pound senior linebacker picked up a fumble by Katella's 
Willie Demyers and ran 21 yards to give Century a 14-7 lead with 6 minutes 47 
seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Armendariz intercepted a Sal Viramontes pass with 6:02 left in the game. It 
was one of seven turnovers for Katella on the night. 
</P>
<P>
 "Some teams are like that," Brown said. "That's been the story of their 
season." 
</P>
<P>
 Viramontes scored on a two-yard run with 51 seconds left in the first quarter 
for Katella. Baltazar Vega set up the touchdown with a 59-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Century tied the score in the second quarter on an 18-yard touchdown pass from 
Stanley Villanueva to Ignacio Vega. Vega also kicked a 17-yard field goal in 
the fourth quarter. RUSSELL BANKS 
</P>
</TEXT>
