<HEADLINE>
<P>
LITTLE GUY STEALS THE SHOW IN NOTRE DAME'S BIG VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trailing, 10-0, Notre Dame got some big help from the shortest guy on the 
Knights' roster -- Corey Franzini. 
</P>
<P>
 Franzini, a 5-foot-5 senior defensive back, intercepted two of Jason Brennan's 
passes in the second quarter to set up two touchdowns and help the Knights to a 
28-10 Mission League victory over Bishop Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame plays host to Chaminade next Friday night with the league title on 
the line. 
</P>
<P>
 Brennan completed 25 of 52 passes for 298 yards, but he threw four 
interceptions and was sacked six times. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame's John Garcia rushed for 152 yards in 24 carries and scored on a 
four-yard run following Franzini's first interception. Garcia also scored on a 
12-yard run late in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame took a 14-10 lead with 30 seconds left in the half when Ryan Bowne 
hit Troy Garner with a 13-yard pass. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowne, who completed 10 of 16 passes for 92 yards, connected with Robbie 
Brewster on a 16-yard scoring pass play to give the Knights a 21-10 lead in the 
third quarter. Brewster caught six passes for 74 yards and had Notre Dame's 
other two interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
 Bishop Montgomery's Omar Smith caught 12 passes for 141 yards. BRIAN CHALEW 
</P>
</TEXT>
