<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEFENSE SPARKS VENTURA, 31-16 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three interceptions and Chris Ryan's 42-yard return of a blocked punt for a 
touchdown sparked Ventura High to a 31-16 Channel League victory over Santa 
Barbara on Friday night at Ventura, keeping the Cougars' playoff hopes alive. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan's return midway through the first quarter was set up when Donell Wickett 
blocked a punt on the Dons' opening possession. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt White's 36-yard field goal with 9:33 left in the second quarter gave 
Ventura (4-5, 4-2 in league play) a 10-0 halftime lead. On the first play of 
the third quarter, Oscar Tovar's interception and 22-yard return set up Brian 
Bushnell's 10-yard score to extend the lead to 17-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Later in the quarter, Eric Olson intercepted a pass and returned it 36 yards 
to set up a one-yard scoring run by Aaron Davis. Eric Blair added a 25-yard 
scoring run in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons (5-3-1, 3-2-1) rushed for only 16 yards. LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</TEXT>
