<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; SYLMAR MARCHES ALONG, 55-18 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG ANAPOL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Greg Marquez controlled the first half, and sophomore running back 
Tyrone Morgan sparked Sylmar High in the second half as the Spartans pounded 
North Hollywood, 55-18, in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game Friday night at 
Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar, playing without four suspended defensive starters, registered seven 
sacks.The 18 points Sylmar allowed is a season high. 
</P>
<P>
 Marquez threw first-half touchdown passes to four receivers. He connected with 
Durell Price for a 57-yard touchdown on the Spartans' second play from 
scrimmage and fired a 27-yarder to Galdino Cortes on the team's second 
possession. 
</P>
<P>
 Marquez also threw a 14-yard touchdown pass to Mike Cervantes and added a 
31-yard scoring pass play to Kevin Brown as Sylmar (9-0, 6-0) built a 27-6 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Marquez completed seven of 13 for 165 yards with one interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Morgan scored on runs of 61, 51 and eight yards. He finished with 148 yards in 
six carries, all in the second half. Sylmar finished with 458 yards, 293 coming 
on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood (2-7, 2-4) was led by wide receiver Ryan Jones, who caught all 
six of quarterback Jesus Acosta's completions, and had scoring receptions of 
six, five and 80 yards. Jones finished with 118 yards in receptions. GREG 
ANAPOL 
</P>
</TEXT>
