<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; ALPHA LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAUREN PETERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kilpatrick 15, L.A. Baptist 14 -- Senior tailback Mario Qualls rushed for a 
season-high 223 yards and two touchdowns in 31 carries to propel Kilpatrick 
(7-2, 3-1) at Alemany High. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls rushed six times for 90 yards -- including a 53-yard scoring run -- on 
a decisive fourth-quarter drive.Qualls' touchdown and a two-point conversion 
pass to Shawn Reed from Qualls put the Mustangs (7-2, 3-1) ahead, 15-14, with 
nine minutes to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls also scored Kilpatrick's first touchdown late in the second quarter to 
cut L.A. Baptist's lead to 14-7. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist (3-6, 3-1), which had won three in a row after opening with five 
losses, scored two touchdowns in the first quarter. Chris Ross rushed for 85 
yards and and a 25-yard touchdown in 15 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick's Cleo Cloman recovered a fumble and recorded a sack. LAUREN 
PETERSON 
</P>
