<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; MARMONTE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA GRALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agoura 41, Camarillo 21 -- Tommy Kim rushed for 250 yards and three touchdowns 
in 13 carries and teammate Steve Parle added 156 yards and two touchdowns in 10 
carries to lead host Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura (4-5, 4-2) rushed for 434 yards.Quarterback Eric Fitzgerald also 
contributed to the team's 519-yard offensive barrage by completing five of 11 
passes for 85 yards and one touchdown, an eight-yard pass to wide receiver Dan 
Weikel that extended Agoura's lead to 26-7 early in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura opened up a 19-7 lead at halftime behind Kim's three touchdown runs. 
The tailback opened with scoring with a 90-yard run and added scores of two and 
three yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo quarterback Joe Borchard completed 11 of 23 passes for 107 yards and 
two touchdowns, both to wide receiver Colin Foutz. The scores covered 27 and 
nine yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo (1-8, 0-6) was also sparked by linebacker Roth Valencia, who 
recovered a fumble and returned it 91 yards for a touchdown in the fourth 
quarter. The Scorpions finished with 210 total yards. LISA GRALL 
</P>
