<HEADLINE>
<P>
ST. FRANCIS WINS MISSION CROSS-COUNTRY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Juniors Kevin Koeper and Andy Van Orden placed first and second to pace the 
St. Francis High boys' cross-country team to victory in the Mission League 
finals at Crescenta Valley Park on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Koeper timed 15 minutes 48 seconds over the three-mile course to tie the 
school record set by Froylan Sanchez in 1992.Van Orden (16:17) was one of five 
Golden Knights to place among the top nine finishers. St. Francis won with 22 
points. Loyola was second with 42, followed by Notre Dame (95) and Alemany 
(115). 
</P>
<P>
 Louisville junior Shalluin Fullove won the girls' race in 19:15. Flintridge 
Sacred Heart placed first with 57 points, followed by Louisville (66), 
Chaminade (70), Harvard-Westlake (96) and Notre Dame (97). 
</P>
</TEXT>
