<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA: SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; PACIFICA ROLLS UP BIG FIRST-HALF LEAD, 
ROUTS LA QUINTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tommy Summers rushed for three touchdowns as Pacifica scored 39 first-half 
points en route to a 45-0 rout of La Quinta in Garden Grove League play Friday 
at Bolsa Grande High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Summers scored on runs of two, 16 and four yards as the Mariners (5-4, 3-2) 
scored touchdowns the first six times they touched the ball, including four 
offensive possessions and fumble recoveries by Donald Douglass and Jeff Burt. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica's defense held the Aztecs (1-8, 0-6) to minus-5 yards total offense 
in the first half and 64 yards total. La Quinta did not cross midfield until 
the Mariners fumbled a ball in their territory with less than one minute 
remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica kept its playoff hopes alive with limited but effective use of its 
first-string attack. Ryan Johansen completed four of six passes for 84 yards -- 
including a 22-yard touchdown strike to Rich Campos late in the second quarter 
-- and did not attempt a pass in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Summers carried nine times for 93 yards before giving way to Eric Westlund, 
who took the Mariners the rest of the way with 85 yards in 17 carries. ANDY 
EISER 
</P>
</TEXT>
