<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; NORTHRIDGE OVERPOWERS UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Missy Clements had 15 kills as Cal State Northridge defeated UC Irvine, 15-9, 
15-6, 15-11, in a nonconference women's volleyball match Friday night at 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the second in a row for Northridge (14-7) and its fourth in 
five matches. 
</P>
<P>
 Clements, a 5-foot-11 senior outside hitter, is 18 kills away from becoming 
Northridge's career leader with 1,327. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Anderson had 10 kills, 10 digs and four blocks for the Matadors while 
setter Kathleen Shannon had 36 assists and 11 digs. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge will play Cal Poly San Luis Obispo in its final home match of the 
season tonight at 7. WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
 Crespi 39, St. Francis 11 -- The Celts broke three school records in the 
Mission League victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Scarcelli scored 15 goals and Pete Driscoll made 22 saves for Crespi, 
both school records. Crespi (15-10, 6-3) also broke the school record of 31 
goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard Westlake 23, Loyola 10 -- Jim Duff, Kirby Kim and Albert Won each 
scored five goals for the Wolverines (19-5) in a Mission League match at 
Loyola. WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 1, El Camino 1 -- Casey Miller scored for the Raiders in a Western 
State Conference match at El Camino College. 
</P>
