<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: WHITACRE TO COACH AT COSTA MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Len Whitacre, who had a successful two-year run at Villa Park High, accepted 
the girls' basketball coaching position at Costa Mesa, the school announced 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Whitacre compiled a 35-11 record with the Spartans after the program had gone 
19-61 the previous four seasons.He takes over a program that played for the 
1993 State championship and has gone 47-12 the last two years. 
</P>
<P>
 Whitacre said one reason he took the job was its proximity to his home in San 
Juan Capistrano and his business in Laguna Hills. Had he been able to sell his 
home -- it was on the market for 18 months -- he would have moved closer to 
Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
 "It has been so difficult to coach, be a father of six children, run a 
business and drive 1 1/2 hours a day," Whitacre said. "This cuts my drive in 
half. That was a major issue." MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Prep Sports 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110594-0297 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 095668 </DOCID>
