<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR LOSES VOLLEYBALL MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Harbor, the No. 1 ranked girls' volleyball team in the State, lost its 
first match of the season, falling to San Jose Archbishop Mitty, 15-4, 16-14, 
11-15, 15-6, in the quarterfinals of the Santa Barbara tournament Friday at 
Santa Barbara High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors (19-1), played the quarterfinal match without setter Jenny Hecker, 
who played in the first-round victory over San Jose Leland Friday morning, but 
returned to Newport Harbor because she was a member of the homecoming court. 
</P>
<P>
 Misty May, who normally plays outside hitter, filled in at setter, but the 
Sailors were out of sync. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach and Corona del Mar also won their first-round matches and lost in 
the quarterfinals. All three schools will play for fifth place when the 
tournament concludes today. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Golden West League girls' tennis finals: 
</P>
<P>
 Rosary sweeps -- Rosary's Eleanor Luzano defeated Judy Esmero of Westminster, 
6-2, 7-5, to win the singles title. Luzano is 50-2 this season, including 28-0 
in league play. Rosary's Cheryl Hamilton and Colleen Coady, who are 22-0 this 
season, won the doubles title. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills dominates -- Top-seeded Lara Spica defeated teammate Margaux 
Pierog, 4-6, 6-3, 6-1 to win the singles title. In an all-Dana Hills doubles 
final, the Michele Johnson and Katie Tierney defeated Lauren Kirby and Karlie 
Noyes, 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 Ruldolph wins singles title again -- Sunny Hills' Dana Ruldolph won the league 
singles title for the second consecutive year, defeating teammate Barbie 
Bayless, 6-0, 6-4. Ruldolph also beat Bayless in last year's final. Troy's Nao 
Kondo and Dana Kim won the doubles title. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Wright wins singles title -- Orange Lutheran's Lori Wright defeated Calvary 
Chapel's Julianne Eastman, 6-1, 6-4, to win the singles title. In an 
all-Connelly doubles final, Cari Winkler and Mera Kriz beat Mimi Nguyen and 
Rani Singh, 6-0, 4-6, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Rosenthal wins title -- Los Alamitos' Melissa Rosenthal defeated Huntington 
Beach's Allison Arvizu, 6-4, 6-1, to win the singles title. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Freeway League girls' volleyball playoff: 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 3, Fullerton 0 -- Jenny Gadd had 14 kills as host Troy (9-7) earned a 
Southern Section playoff berth with a 15-8, 15-13, 15-13 sweep. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Pacific Coast League girls' volleyball playoff: 
</P>
<P>
 University 3, Estancia 2 -- Courtney Chase had 23 kills and Andrea Iliescu 
added 20 for University, which defeated Estancia, 11-15, 15-4, 7-15, 15-4, 
15-13, in a playoff for third place. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Academy League: 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 3, Capistrano Valley Christian 2 -- Emily Hallenbeck had 19 
kills to lead St. Margaret's (9-5, 3-3) over Capistrano Valley Christian 15-13, 
2-15, 12-15, 15-10, 15-13. St. Margaret's won the league title because of two 
victories over Capistrano Valley Christian (9-5, 3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange League water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 15, Valencia 2 -- Tad Murphy's scored seven goals to set a school 
single-season scoring record for Brea-Olinda (22-4, 8-0). Murphy has 108 goals, 
breaking Ray Schwengel's record of 106 in 1988. The victory also gave the 
Wildcats a record for games won in a season, breaking the 1990 mark of 21. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 11, Servite 9 -- Mike Stanley scored five goals, John Zin added 
three and Peter Lange recorded 17 saves to lead host Esperanza, ranked fifth in 
the county. 
</P>
